<mod:findName type="event" name="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS_CREW">
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="unique_vance" blue="false">
		<text>Vance Wentworth Prime</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Vance Wentworth Prime
			Titles: Leader of The Multiversal Rebellion, (Former) Federation Admiral, Veteran of The Mantis-Federation War, CEO of Wentworth Industries
			Species: Human - Age: 75 - Gender: Male
			
			Vance Prime is a complicated figure. There's enough to be said about him to fill a whole library: he started the biggest insurrection the multiverse has ever seen, ruined the lives of countless people, and made an all-consuming monster in the Rebellion which cannot be contained or permanently stopped by this point. The fact that you agreed to give him a second chance either speaks to your compassion or your folly.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_unique_mantis_queen" blue="false">
		<text>Leikonpliiinakra</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Queen Leikonpliiinakra
			Title: Queen of the Mantis Hive
			Species: Mantis - Age: 80 - Gender: Female
			
			The current queen of the Mantis Hive, Queen Leikonpliiinakra was the one responsible for allying the Hive with the Coalition, something she regrets but is unable to do much to reverse with the current economic crisis wrecking the Hive. Hopefully that can begin to change now. 
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="unique_cyra" blue="false">
		<text>Cyra Black</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Cyra Black
			Titles: Caretaker of the Protectorate, Original MFK Ace
			Species: Human - Age: 74 - Gender: Female
			
			One of the two original MFKs, Cyra Black is the main person in charge of protecting the Protectorate and keeping Vance's nephew, Jerry Wentworth, safe and sound. She's extremely loyal to Vance and is his closest companion, second only to his nephew. They were close enough to the point of having an affair in the past.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="FR_LIST_CREW_LEAH" blue="false">
		<text>Leah Applebuzz</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Leah Applebuzz
			Titles: The Beam Master, Your Nemesis
			Species: Human - Age: 24 - Gender: Female
			
			The daughter of Count Dinkleman Reichster Von Applebuzz Tri Tri the Fourth, and your personal nemesis. What she lacks in common sense and strategy, she more than makes up for in pure determination. It seems something you said to her has swayed her to your side, so now you two are problably more frenemies than nemeses.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_unique_sammy" blue="false">
		<text>Michael Stepford</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Michael Stepford
			Title: (Former) Mascot For Sammy The Spider
			Species: Human - Age: 20 - Gender: Male
			
			The actor for Sammy The Spider, or at least he *was* the actor for the character until a close encounter with Stephan dressed as Ellie the Equinoid left him traumatized and unable to work for Flowers and Sunshine anymore. He got the gig thanks to playing Ellie at birthday party for Jerry Wentworth, Vance's newphew.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_gozer" blue="false">
		<text>Goziodeon</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Goziodeon Lar Auilacus
			Title: Leader of the Haunts
			Species: Alpha Vagabond (More specifically a Poltergeist) - Age: 666 - Gender: N/A
			
			The Haunt's head honcho, the biggest and strongest criminal organization in this side of the Dynasty. Born just after the collapse of the Obelisk empire, Goziodeon enjoyed an early life of luxury and success in his family business before the Great Dynasty Depression hit, causing him to turn to a life of crime in order to survive. Turns out he had a knack for running criminal organizations, and in a few centuries managed to build an empire of crime that could match and surpass any pirate organization if only he ever dared to leave Specter territory.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="human_humanoid" blue="false">
		<text>Stefan Richard</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Stefan Richard
			Title: Minelauncher Salesman
			Species: Human - Age: 42 - Gender: Male
			
			There's not much to say about Stefan. He inherited his minelauncher store in a quaint station in Federation territory; business was going well until a feak accident caused the station he lived and worked on to be transported across timelines, ending up in a land completely foreign to his own, filled with alien species he'd never heard of and weapons that made no sense to him.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_unique_jon" blue="false">
		<text>Jon Briggs</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Jon Briggs
			Title: Lead Wentworth Technician, Multiversal Rebel
			Species: Human - Age: 45 - Gender: Male
			
			Jon is one of the most well known technicians within Wentworth Innovations: his expertise when it comes to drones is unparalleled. In fact, drone booster technology was actually something he perfected. It is easily installed on any ships with high enough drone control levels without the need for any external augments. While he came to this universe from Universe 1, Jon's actual birtplace is unkown, implying that every Jon seems to make that decision in one point or another in their life.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_unique_purple_beard" blue="false">
		<text>Purple Beard</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Clint Sheerman
			Title: (Now Former) Dread Pirate Purple Beard, (Former) Legionnaire Captain of the 45th Division, Pirate Legend
			Species: Human - Age: 65 - Gender: Male
			
			Clint was born and raised in Universe 1. From a very young age, he was trained to be a Rebel soldier. He was taken from his family after turning 10 by Vance One himself and ever since then has trained every day to become a Legionnaire. While he did climb the ranks of the Legion very quickly, his career halted when he was forced to do an act that, to this day, he refuses to ever mention or elaborate upon. Whatever it was, it was so brutal that it broke his faith in the Rebellion. He faked his own death and fled Universe 1 by jerryrigging a MV drive to his trusty legion assault ship. Uninterested in joining any other faction, Clint turned to piracy, quickly making a name for himself and earning the moniker "Purple Beard". The rest, as they say, is history.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="spider_venom" blue="false">
		<text>The Venomous Spider Queen</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Charlotte
			Title: Venomous Spider Queen
			Species: Mutated Giant Alien Spider - Age: 20 - Gender: Female
			
			While similar to the the regular Giant Alien Spider Queen, this specific specimen can excrete powerful venom which can easily incapacitate even the hardiest Rockman. She is unable to produce any eggs, however, so she can never create her own brood: a fact that might contribute to her affection for all things spider.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="pony_engi" blue="false">
		<text>The Cyberpony</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: 3QU3STR14
			Title: Cybernetic Pony
			Species: Engi - Age: 80 - Gender: N/A
			
			Not much is known about this strange Engi. All that we know is that they love pretending to be a pony and would be very hurt if someone were to tell them that they aren't, in fact, a pony.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reborn_slimer" blue="false">
		<text>Slimer</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Slimer Ssstriel the 3rd
			Titles: (Former) King of the Kleptocracy, Revenant Guard
			Species: Revenant Slug - Age: 254 - Gender: Hermaphrodite (culturally male)
			
			A old and now dead king of the Kleptocracy back when it was called the "Collective Slug Kleptocracy". His rule was so cruel that it caused the Kleptocracy to become a republic for almost 100 years. His death came thanks to food poisoning caused by a nasty batch of hallucinogenic melons, orchestrated by his own son.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reborn_phys" blue="false">
		<text>Phys</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Phys Karvar
			Title: The Ion Shriker, Revenant Mascot
			Species: Revenant Shell - Age: 151 - Gender: Female
			
			The Shell goverment once proposed a new research department that failed right after its inception. Phys, the first living test of their project, died shortly after being 'born' and took over the whole facility along with all of its research to make more of herself. She enjoys making others happy and is no longer in constant pain after being freed from her curse.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reborn_aleenor" blue="false">
		<text>Aleenor</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Aleenor Lakitrapikk
			Title: Mantis Bishop, Revenant Striker
			Species: Revenant Mantis - Age: 210 - Gender: Female
			
			One of the most loyal Bishops chosen by Queen Latrakkpkat to be the caretaker of the hatchery in the deepest part of the Mantis Hive capital. Her life didn't consist of much besides her job, but she died protecting the eggs from the Great Hatchery Fire of the Silver Age, a tragedy that took the lives of millions of Mantis and could have ended the empire as a whole if not for Aleenor's quick thinking and sacrifice. Her name is still revered in the Mantis Hive and she even has a holiday dedicated to her.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reborn_vin" blue="false">
		<text>Vin</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Vin Vytredonn
			Title: Rock Paladin, Revenant Enforcer
			Species: Revenant Rockman - Age: 450 - Gender: Male
			
			A Rock Paladin who served and lived through a very peaceful period of the Rock Theocracy, his strength wasn't noteworthy and he didn't acomplish much in life. In fact, the most noteworthy thing about him was how he died. His autopilot went haywire while he was sleeping, sending him straight into a nearby red giant. Needless to say, he wasn't happy being bossed around by G.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reborn_cleo" blue="false">
		<text>Cleo</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Cleo Smith
			Title: MFK Ace, Revenant Listener
			Species: Revenant Human - Age: 70 - Gender: Male
			
			The youngest revenant in G's team, and the least stable too. After his brutal death at the hands of a modified repair drone, this ex-MFK Ace is now just a shattered shell of who he once was. He wasn't a noteworthy Ace so his death was covered up by the Rebellion, his name becoming nothing more than a old legend to scare new recruits.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reborn_zulu" blue="false">
		<text>Zulu</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Zulu The Radiant
			Title: Revenant Right Hand
			Species: Revenant Lanius - Age: ??? - Gender: N/A
			
			The first revenant and G's old friend. Their death is what caused G's spiral into necromancy in the vain hope of bringing them back to life. Now they only exist to extend G's will, serving her unconditionally. That is, until you broke her curse and saved them.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reborn_g" blue="false">
		<text>G</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: G The Necrolich
			Title: Revenant Leader, Necrolich, (Former) Obelisk Royal Navigator
			Species: Revenant Obelisk - Age: Roughly 100000 - Gender: N/A (Culturally Female)
			
			The Obelisk Royal in charge of charting other universes, G was a loyal worker under Queen Y for all her life, and even in death she still hopes she can see her queen in person again. After the death of her close friend Zulu, G spiraled into a deep depression, unfortunately replaced by a dark ambition once she found the Necronomicon.   
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reformed_frostwall" blue="false">
		<text>Frostwall</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Frostwall Dymondesh
			Title: (Former) Sentinel, Revenant Preacher
			Species: Revenant Crystal - Age: 580 - Gender: Male
			
			A skilled Sentinel who had a bright future ahead of him until he was sent on a mission to recover a valuable Crystal weapon cargo from the hands of a strange gray ship, one that resembled the Utopians' work. But something about it changed Frostwall. His mind fell to the incessant whispers and he was put down shortly after.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reformed_deathbloom" blue="false">
		<text>Deathbloom</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Deathbloom Y'Cirtil
			Title: (Former) Treasure Hunter, Revenant Seeker
			Species: Revenant Oro'bache - Age: 208 - Gender: Female
			
			Deathbloom's name might sound aggressive and murder-y, but the truth is that she was one of the kindest Vampweeds you could find outside of the Confederancy. In fact, she rarely even visited Vampweed-controlled sectors, usually only dropping in to sell her valuable artifacts. After her death, the system had to be quarantined as her spores somehow adapted to the vacuum of space and became deadlier each cycle. Now they are the deadliest biohazard known to the Vampweeds.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="FR_LIST_CREW_MORPHS_POK" blue="false">
		<text>Pok</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: POK DOK
			Title: Forbidden Experiment, Revenant Infiltrator
			Species: Revenant Morph - Age: ??? - Gender: N/A
			
			Pok would be the most powerful Infiltrator unit if they weren't just a little guy. They hate violence and just want to be friends with others. Unfortunately, they are forced to obey The Watcher's commands.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reformed_charror" blue="false">
		<text>CHARROR</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Character-Error
			Title: (Former) Defender, Revenant Hacker
			Species: Revenant Engi - Age: ??? - Gender: N/A
			
			T̷̢̓H̵͕̓Ḙ̵̈ ̷̣̍E̷͇̎Y̸͎̋Ḛ̷́ ̸̙͋Ŕ̸̩Í̴̙S̸̺͑E̵͈̓Ş̸͊ ̷̖̽T̴͙̅Ḩ̵͆R̴̳͐O̶͓̎U̶̻͒G̵͈̓H̵͉̊ ̴̩̉T̶̪͂H̷̳̚E̷̺̽ ̸͈̽C̵̜͑L̵̡̓O̸̗̓Ű̵̠Ḍ̸̔S̶̩͂ ̷̝̇Ô̸͖F̷͔͘ ̸̼̅O̴̫͗U̵͓̾R̸̠̀ ̵̡̇C̵̝̿Ò̵̙N̴̺̔Ś̷̖C̵̼̒Į̶̐Ô̴͉Ű̵ͅS̸̮̅N̶̺͆E̷̬̓S̷͕̾S̵͚͛ ̵̝̀-̶̛̯ ̷̟̿T̷̝͝H̴̺͐E̷̟͆ ̸̞͝E̶̠͆N̸͕͂D̶̜̔ ̶̗̊P̸̮͑R̴͖̅O̵̢͝M̵̙̂Ị̶̂S̴̯͋S̷̺̈E̷̜̕D̵̰̔ ̴͙́Ẅ̵̪́Ỉ̶̪L̷͎̂L̶̬̀ ̴̪́Ị̷̿N̵͉͝D̵̙̿E̷̮̅N̷̝̒T̷̳͛ ̸͕́Ḧ̴̢́E̵̜̿R̸̨͘ ̴̱͌W̴̜͑I̵̧̒Ḽ̵̏L̶̳͌ ̷̤̔A̸̯̔Ș̸̆ ̵͉̓T̵͓̄H̴̜̀Ȅ̴̝ ̵̥̒V̵͖̆Ì̷̧S̶̡̈́Ȃ̶̞G̷͚̕Ȇ̷̩ ̶͇̒Ț̶̆Ȇ̸̤A̵̭̍R̸̤͊S̵̘̀ ̸̘̋T̸͚̓H̶̝̓R̴̯͊O̸͇̊Ű̷̲G̴̺͘Ḧ̶́͜ ̵̡̋O̷͉͐Ȗ̷͍R̵̩̆ ̴͚̈́F̴̝͌A̴̧̕B̵̧̋R̵̩͂I̴̻̒C̵͙̊Ă̸̱T̵̳̍Ẹ̸̈́Ḓ̸̔ ̸̪͊R̶̨̄Ë̸̹́Ą̷́L̸͕͛I̶͚͠T̴̙̽Y̸̦̏.̶̪̀ ̵͈̽S̸̭͂O̴͗͜ ̸̪͑R̷͕̎E̶̩͊S̴̥͑T̷͓̃ ̵̞̀F̷̢́Ọ̸̀R̵̘̎ ̵̢͊T̶̬̂H̶̹̏Ê̷̜ ̷̩̊S̶̳͒T̸̙̏Ó̵̯R̵̙̄M̴̛͜ ̴̡̉S̵͕͋H̸̙͌Ä̸̖L̶͓̎L̵̜̆ ̵͈̀S̵͎͝P̴̣̊A̸̤͝R̸̗͠E̸̝͗ ̶̡͘N̷̢̔Ȍ̶̺ ̶̞̔B̸̦͌O̶͈͝A̸͕͝T̷̬̒.̸̮͐
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reformed_leo" blue="false">
		<text>Leo</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Leonardo Lerpae
			Title: (Former) Eargen Enforcer, Revenant Spec-Ops
			Species: Revenant Leech - Age: 149 - Gender:  Male
			
			Leo never really wanted to be a fighter: in fact, his dream was to open a outpost that specialized in painting ships at low prices without sacrificing quality. Unfortunately, once the Republic started a war with the Theocracy, Leo was conscripted into the army and so his fate was sealed.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_reformed_searak" blue="false">
		<text>Searak</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Searak Fray
			Title: (Former) Duskbringer, Revenant Bomber
			Species: Revenant Zoltan - Age: 81 - Gender: Male
			
			One of the first Duskbringers to fight for the cause, Searak joined the movement after the death of his brother, Kirak, was glossed over during the original civil war, his name denied the valor of his sacrifice. After going mad thanks to Her influence, all the Duskbringer can see now is the pain and hatred he carried in life.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_watcher" blue="false">
		<text>The Watcher</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: 				   YOU
			Title:				 		ARE
			Species: 			   TIRED
			
			REST			 	NOW
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_bonus_augustus" blue="false">
		<text>Augustus</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Augustus Goldicus Shinan the 5th
			Title: The Ghost With The Most, Revenant Exile
			Species: Revenant Phantom Alpha - Age: 985 - Gender: N/A (Culturally Male)
			
			The richest Phantom in the universe, his endless scrap reserves are enough to buy a whole sector! Something which he *did* want to do before his own hubris brought his downfall after skimping on hundreds of safety regulations and perishing under the explosion of his own anti-bio weapons factory.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="FR_LIST_CREW_SALLY" blue="false">
		<text>Sally</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Sally Finch Morrey
			Title: (Former) Arcadia Scientist, Revenant Researcher
			Species: Revenant Spider Experiment - Age: 90 - Gender: Female
			
			Sally was a brilliant biotech scientist who was close to developing a way of preventing crew skill degradation before a terrible illness took her life. However, just before she passed, she managed to upload her mind and consciousness into her Giant Alien Spider companion Finch. Now, with her human days behind her, she searches for her own place in this vast multiverse. 
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_bonus_prince" blue="false">
		<text>Prince</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Prince of Darkness
			Title: Prince of the Demonic Realm, Revenant Sponsor
			Species: Revenant Demonic Equinoid - Age: ??? - Gender: Male
			
			While not a literal religious demon, the being possessing this equinoid fits the bill to a T. Summoned from a universe where demonic creatures walk the earth, this being is willing to do anything... for a price. That price usually being your soul.  
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_bonus_tririac" blue="false">
		<text>Tririac</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Tririac
			Title: (Former) Thing 4, Revenant Supplier
			Species: Revenant Thing - Age: Ageless - Gender: Irrelevant
			
			Almost nothing is known about this being. All we know is that they once served Her but rebelled and defected once they learned the true reason for Her plans. Now all they care about is destroying Her and all of Her servants completely. 
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="fr_unique_daisy" blue="false">
		<text>Bellrennis</text>
		<event>
			<text>PROFILE: Bellrennis 
			Title: Lead Scientist In Commonwealth Exploration And Research
			Species: Obelisk - Age: Roughly 90000 (at the time of death) - Gender: N/A (culturally female)
			
			Bellrennis, also known as Daisy, was the lead researching in weapons and drones for the Refuge. Her work was far superior to her peers but her ambitions were too great for the small place that was the Refuge. She wanted to explore the outside, to find allies for her people's cause. Her status as a potential security threat made her so controversial that it created a schism in the Refuge. She left the system but unfortunately didn't make very far before the Royals caught up with her, killing her and leaving her cruiser adrift as a grim reminder of their might.
			</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK_STATUS"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
</mod:findName>

